## Copy this file to `.env.local` and set exactly one base URL.
## `.env.local` is ignored by git and is the file each teammate should edit locally.

## Local backend on the same machine (iOS simulator / web):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/

## Android emulator talking to a backend running on your Mac:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:3000/

## Physical device on the same Wi-Fi network:
## Replace the IP with your computer's local network IP.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.20:3000/

## Shared staging / production backend:
## Must use HTTPS. Non-local HTTP URLs are rejected by `src/config/env.ts`.
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.example.com/
